			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					New gaming/media system: PC/Laptop/xbox/playstation
				</h2>
				

						
							
							
							
						
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1821646">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Just moved into a new place.  Will be getting a new TV and am thinking about getting a game system to go along with it.<br />
<br />
Reddit is a goldmine but figured I'd ask Graffe's too.  <br />
<br />
Recommendations can be pie-in-the-sky as far as costs go, but keep in mind that I am not a high-volume gamer.  I play maybe 3 games per year, which includes lots of re-plays of classic games on emulators.  The one &quot;modern&quot; game I am looking to play is Dark Souls, which is several years old so I'm not worried.  Would be nice to have a machine that can play a current game, though.<br />
<br />
I am thinking of buying either a PC or a Gaming Laptop and one console (An Xbox or Playstation).  The console would also function as a media center for watching movie and netflix and such.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
