			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: New gaming/media system: PC/Laptop/xbox/playstation
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1821653">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							You don't want to build a PC until October/November, when the next round of CPU's and video cards will be released. Even if you don't pick one of those up, the prices on the current stuff will drop significantly.<br />
<br />
As for PS4 vs. XB1, the difference is what kind of games you want to play.<br />
<br />
The PS4 has more single player oriented titles and Japanese titles, but their online experience isn't as good as on the XB1 (although due to fanboy over-reaction, the PS4 has more sales, so more online players).<br />
<br />
The XB1 gets pretty massive patches monthly that add new features, or resolve bugs.  One of the main things hindering development right now is the lack of release for DirectX 12.  DirectX 12 makes handling video textures much simpler, so programmers can just use DX12 and don't have to learn how to correctly handle texture memory.  PS4 users still can't play mp3's.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
