				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: New gaming/media system: PC/Laptop/xbox/playstation
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1821773">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Ditto what Nadiar said.  Unless you need a laptop for mobility, I suggest building your own desktop.  You will get a better system cheaper than buying a laptop and it will last longer than a laptop because of wear on the system from the heat.  I went through a nice gaming laptop in under two years because it was on like 12 hours a day every day for school and even used a cooling fan pad with it.  While I did buy a new gaming <a href="http://www.overclock.net/lists/display/view/id/5641506" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">laptop</a> that is better than my desktop, I don't use it nearly as much because it is for when I am on the road or at a client's facilities (I use it for development not gaming... so far anyway).<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.microcenter.com/product/437205/Core_i7-5960X_30_GHz_LGA_2011-V3_Boxed_Processor" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Intel has 8 core processors</a> out now, but I am not sure I would spend the money on them just yet.  Whatever you do, buy the best <a href="http://www.asus.com/Motherboards/RAMPAGE_V_EXTREME/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">motherboard</a> (okay yeah I think this mobo is a bit over the top, but...) you can get that you can upgrade with more memory and faster CPU down the road when prices drop.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
