						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Is is possible to get a compact design for the desktop?  I don't really need mobility (I have laptops I can play old games on when I'm on the road, etc.); but living space is a premium where I live (an off-street parking spot alone is $200/month) and I'd prefer to have a PC that is as small as it can possibly be without sacrificing performance.  At this point, I don't mind so much not having space for extra hard drives and specialty cards and such so long as the base system is capable.  I'd rather have a more compact, easily-moved machine.
