				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: New gaming/media system: PC/Laptop/xbox/playstation
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1821839">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Goladus</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=149cbade0a7528e5bf86db302341cae8&amp;p=1821809#post1821809" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Is is possible to get a compact design for the desktop?  I don't really need mobility (I have laptops I can play old games on when I'm on the road, etc.); but living space is a premium where I live (an off-street parking spot alone is $200/month) and I'd prefer to have a PC that is as small as it can possibly be without sacrificing performance.  At this point, I don't mind so much not having space for extra hard drives and specialty cards and such so long as the base system is capable.  I'd rather have a more compact, easily-moved machine.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>There's no reason to not put it on a shelf somewhere on the wall, take advantage of z-axis space. I wouldn't try to minimize case space though, or at least if you are going to not use a case at all so that air flow isn't compromised.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
