				<div class="message">I was typing a longer reply, but how about instead you find me a popular system from one of those reddits that has an airflow problem that isn't indicated in a response.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Assuming I am not designing this configuration to optimize for this context and I choose the parts optimizing for a workstation/gaming context, or perhaps a system that does all 3 contexts simultaneously well (in a HTPC context we would want a lot of disk space somewhere in our network), then all of the builds will have air flow problems, even in the context of a full tower air flow is a problem, especially if we do not want the system to be very loud (my main issue with such systems). I would just put this on a shelf though so it would not be an issue assuming someone doesn't find the system being in view an eyesore.
						</blockquote>
